==English==
===Verb===
'''to [[abide]] [[by]]'''
#{{transitive}} To [[accept]] a [[decision]] or [[law]] and [[act]] in [[accordance]] with it; to [[conform]] to; to [[acquiesce]]; as, ''to abide by an award.''
#{{transitive}} To [[remain]] [[faithful]] to something or someone; to [[stand to]]; to [[adhere]].
#*'''Quotations'''
#:The poor fellow was obstinate enough '''to abide by''' what he said at first - [[Fielding]]

